        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-30T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-30T04:00:00-05:00" n="1518" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1518">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.8576/6–3049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cabot</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-30T17:00:00+08:00">June 30, 1949—5 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 30—9:42 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2570. Reliable source states that Chen Yi has recommended tongs being against
                    plan to rush Consulate reported in mytel 2466, June 24, repeated Nanking 1331,
                    and 2536 June 29, repeated Nanking 1382.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2570, repeated Nanking 1409.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cabot</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
